AMEND S e n ate Bill No. 773 House Bill No. 735*
by deleting all the language after the enacting clause and substituting:
SECTION 1. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 13-3-401, is amended by adding the
following new, appropriately designated subdivision:
( ) "Submission" means:
(A) With respect to a development plan, the date on which an applicant
submits to a local government a complete application for approval of the
development plan; or
(B) With respect to a building permit, the date on which an applicant
submits to a local government a complete application for approval of the building
permit.
SECTION 2. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 13-3-413, is amended by adding the
following new subsections:
( ) Notwithstanding this section to the contrary:
(1) A vesting period applicable to a development plan approved by a
local government must not expire earlier than three (3) years following the later of
the date on which the appeal period for challenging such approval has expired or
the date on which all appeals of such approval have been exhausted; and
(2) A vesting period applicable to a building permit issued by a local
government must not expire earlier than three (3) years following the later of the
date on which the appeal period for challenging such issuance has expired or the
date on which all appeals of such issuance have been exhausted.
